page.title: 07Seagry Wood.
page.content: In our wood there are a lot of rabbit holes and fox holes.Some of them you cant tell which is a rabbit hole and which is a fox hole. Some of the holes are badgers holes.Badgers eat bulbs, small creatures like mice,rats,earth worms,roots and berries.Foxes eat small creatures and berries.At night foxes hunt for rabbits.They kill lambs but they do not eat them.They take over a rabbit burrow or badgers sets.The badgers are very clean animals.When you go to the wood you can see the badgers foot prints on their setts.The sett in Seagry Wood has been there for 100 years.The tunnels lead to lots of rooms.Some tunnels are left to let fresh air in to the sett.The trees are oak,ash,horse chestnut and sweet chestnut.There are also ferns and fungi.
